comment.body:
@musickiller one day on IRC he said “I will be busy in the weekend, I'll be back on Monday”. But he never showed up again and never told us that he would go away for more than 7 months. So I and a bunch of otherwise very active contributors were just left in the dark, not knowing whether he would come back tomorrow or never. Leaving the projerct without informing contributors is a major mistake, IMHO. You're welcome to having another opinion.
Morphis is kept in a private git repo that is not protected by SSL/TLS. I refuse to create an account on an unprotected site, yes, I didn't ask him for commit privileges (and I don't think I would have gotten it, had I asked, but that's pure speculation).
Coming back after 226+ days of absence, the first thing he does after coming back is to delete a bunch of otherwise relevant comments on the subreddit. That's another major mistake, IMHO. again, you're welcome to having another opinion.
